explanation: The solution utilizes a sorted list of ranges to efficiently track and query ranges.  Adding a range involves finding its insertion point and merging overlapping ranges. Querying a range involves iterating through the sorted list to check for overlaps. Removing a range requires splitting it into non-overlapping ranges and updating the list. This approach provides logarithmic time complexity for addRange and removeRange operations due to binary search, while queryRange has linear time complexity.  The space complexity is linear due to storing the ranges. Energy implications are low as the operations are primarily data structure manipulations.

